The paper deals with visual recognition tasks, specifically age estimation, head pose estimation, multilabel classification, and semantic segmentation. These tasks are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper proposes a new method for learning label distributions using deep ConvNets, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of datasets and evaluation metrics commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.IR.
